text.tspan: Answer 2 : Shared objects don't get FDs.
The problem here is that open shared objects
(dyanmic libraries) are not listed in open file
descriptors. If anybody can run a process with
LD_LIBRARY_PATH set to load libs on cluster
storage they can fail the next DR failover and
Not registered as a CVE but interesting
possibilities. Lsof was removed for timeouts.
